API Gateway
Overview

The API Gateway acts as the single entry point for all client requests in the microservices architecture. 
Instead of calling individual services directly, clients send requests to the API Gateway, which routes them to the appropriate microservice.
The gateway integrates with Eureka Service Discovery to dynamically locate available service instances,
eliminating the need for hard-coded service URLs.


